   <concept id="FAR_31_104" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">31.104</ph> Contracts with educational institutions.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <p class="- topic/p " id="d1936e8">This category includes all contracts and contract modifications for research and development, training, and other work performed by educational institutions (defined as institutions of higher educations in the OMB Uniform Guidance at <ph outputclass="CFR" class="- topic/ph ">2 CFR part 200</ph>, subpart A, and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title20-section1001&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                  scope="external"
                  format="html">20 U.S.C. 1001</xref>).</p>
         <ol id="d1911e22" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1936e18">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
						            The contracting officer shall incorporate the cost principles and procedures in <xref href="Subpart_31.3.dita#FAR_Subpart_31_3"
                        base="i1084503"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  31.3</xref> by reference in cost-reimbursement contracts with educational institutions as the basis for-</p>
               <ol id="d1911e35" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1936e27">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
								                Determining reimbursable costs under the contracts and cost-reimbursement subcontracts thereunder performed by educational institutions;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1936e32">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
								                Negotiating indirect cost rates; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1936e37">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
								                Settling costs of cost-reimbursement terminated contracts (see <xref href="Subpart_49.3.dita#FAR_Subpart_49_3"
                              base="i1068185"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  49.3</xref> and <xref href="49.109-7.dita#FAR_49_109_7"
                              base="i1068898"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">49.109-7</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1936e48">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
						            The cost principles in this subpart are to be used as a guide in evaluating costs in connection with negotiating fixed-price contracts and termination settlements.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
